<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410987>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Prionospio fosterae sp. nov., anterior end and mid-body chaetigers, dorsal view (MNRJP-2748, holotype), showing characteristic color in ethanol.Abbreviations: br, branchia; pe, peristomium; pr, prostomium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4410987/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410989>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. SEM of Prionospio fosterae sp. nov. A. Anterior end and mid-body chaetigers. B. Close-up of the anterior end. C. Hooks (hoods removed). D. Posterior chaetigers and pygidium. Abbreviations: br, branchia; pe, peristomium; pr, prostomium; py, pygidium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4410989/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4410991>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Prionospio fosterae sp. nov. A. Chaetiger 1. B. Chaetiger 2. C. Chaetiger 3. D. Chaetiger 4. E. Anterior capillary chaeta from anterior row. F. Anterior capillary chaeta from posterior row. G. Posterior capillary chaetae. H. Companion capillary chaetae. I. Hooded hook. J. Branchia. K. Pygidium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4410991/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

